Introduction

Shin Ji Min is a South Korean singer, rapper, and lyricist under ALO MALO Entertainment. She was the leader of the girl group AOA and its sub-unit AOA Black. She was also a member of the unit Jimin N J.Don.

On July 4, 2020, FNC Entertainment announced Jimin would be leaving AOA and halting all activities in the entertainment industry following bullying allegations made by former member Mina.

On July 14, 2022, it was announced that Jimin had joined ALO MALO Entertainment and will be returning to the entertainment industry after 2 years, as most rumors were proven false. She released her first solo mini album on February 22, 2023, titled "BOXES", officially returning from her 2-year hiatus.
